{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/web-scraping-korea-baseball-organization-kbo-40bf6210a267", "time": 1683007398.256193, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/web-scraping-korea-baseball-organization-kbo-40bf6210a267/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Web Scraping \u2014 Korea Baseball Organization (KBO) | by John Oh | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Web Scraping \u2014 Korea Baseball Organization (KBO)", "description": "ESPN started to televise Korea Baseball Organization (KBO) games about a week ago, providing live sports actions for the first time since March. Fans who were desperate for live actions, it provided\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://www.espn.com/mlb/story/_/id/29154712/meet-stay-home-dad-turned-international-expert-korean-baseball", "anchor_text": "ESPN article", "paragraph_index": 0}, {"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/web-scraping-nba-stats-4b4f8c525994", "anchor_text": "Web Scraping NBA Stats", "paragraph_index": 10}], "all_paragraphs": ["ESPN started to televise Korea Baseball Organization (KBO) games about a week ago, providing live sports actions for the first time since March. Fans who were desperate for live actions, it provided something. Unless you are a hardcore fan like Dan (ESPN article), you wouldn\u2019t be familiar with KBO teams or players. So, here\u2019s my attempt to provide an introduction into KBO with data science and Python programming.", "The KBO is the highest professional baseball league in South Korea. It started playing in 1982 with six teams and has since expanded to 10 teams. Here are the ten KBO teams and the city where they play their home games.", "Scrap Wiki page to retrieve names of stadiums", "The KBO Wikipage provides several tables, one of which contains team names and stadiums where they play. We can scrap these tables using Pandas\u2019 read_html. Pandas\u2019 read_html provides a neat way of reading tables into a list of DataFrame objects.", "After examining the result, we can see the third table contains Team, City, Stadium, Capacity, and Joined.", "After selecting the third table and replacing the header with the top row, we have a Pandas dataframe that shows stadium info.", "Using geopy\u2019s geocoders, we can just pass the names of stadiums to retrieve latitude and longitude. I had to replace \u201cDaejeon Hanbat Baseball Stadium\u201d to \u201cHanwha Life Eagles Park\u201d as geolocator wasn\u2019t able to recognize the former.", "After we retrieved latitude and longitude of each stadium, we can use folium to create a map of teams where they play.", "Five teams play in or near Seoul, the other five teams play in the southern part of Korea.", "The surrounding Seoul area is zoomed and folium\u2019s marker with team name and the city is showing.", "This article (Web Scraping NBA Stats) provides an excellent tutorial to scrape NBA stats from Basketball reference site. Similarly, we can scrap baseball stats from Baseball-Reference.com as the site provides comprehensive team and player statistics including KBO.", "The below code block scrapes 2020 KBO batting stats into a Pandas dataframe.", "However, the data types of the scraped Pandas dataframe are objects. We can convert non-object types to numeric for later visualization.", "We can now visualize team home runs or any other stats you\u2019d like.", "To summarize, a table from Wikipedia is scraped then used to create a map and current batting stats are scraped from Baseball reference. Hope this provides some valuable info. Below you can find more resources for such as how to watch. Hope you enjoy these live baseball games as well!", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F40bf6210a267&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}